    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secrets Rotation for Claude API Keys"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An API key that never rotates is a key that can be leaked silently for months before anyone notices. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secrets rotation",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the practice of periodically replacing live credentials with new ones while maintaining zero application downtime. For Claude API keys specifically, rotation protects against exfiltration from logs, config snapshots, or compromised developer machines."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Rotate API keys on a schedule, not in response to a breach. A breach-driven rotation happens after the damage is done. A scheduled rotation limits the window of any credential compromise to the rotation interval."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers the zero-downtime rotation sequence, automated rotation tooling, detection of leaked keys before rotation, and the key-per-workload isolation pattern."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Zero-downtime API key rotation sequence: create new key, write alongside old, app refreshes, health check, revoke old",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Zero-Downtime Rotation Requires Two Keys"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Naively rotating a key \u2014 revoke old, issue new, update secret \u2014 creates a gap where requests fail between the revocation and the application picking up the new key. The zero-downtime pattern avoids this by keeping both keys valid during the transition:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Create new key",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " at Anthropic API (old key still active)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Write new key to secrets store",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " alongside the old key (both valid)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Application picks up new key",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " on its next secrets refresh cycle (typically 1h, configurable)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Health-check",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " confirms the new key works \u2014 at least one successful API call with the new key observed"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Revoke old key",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 now safe because all application instances have transitioned"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The rotation window (time between steps 2 and 5) is the overlap period. Size it larger than your secrets refresh interval: if the application refreshes secrets every 60 minutes, the overlap must be at least 90 minutes to ensure all instances have picked up the new key."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secrets Refresh in the Application"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The application must not cache the API key indefinitely. A module-level singleton with a TTL-based refresh picks up rotated keys without a restart:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/api_key.py\nimport os, time, threading\nimport boto3\n\n_lock = threading.Lock()\n_cached_key: str | None = None\n_fetched_at: float = 0.0\nTTL_SECONDS = 3600   # refresh every hour\n\ndef _fetch_from_ssm() -> str:\n    client = boto3.client(\"ssm\", region_name=os.environ[\"AWS_REGION\"])\n    resp = client.get_parameter(\n        Name=os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_KEY_PARAM\"],\n        WithDecryption=True,\n    )\n    return resp[\"Parameter\"][\"Value\"]\n\ndef get_api_key() -> str:\n    \"\"\"Returns the current API key, refreshing from SSM if TTL has expired.\"\"\"\n    global _cached_key, _fetched_at\n    now = time.monotonic()\n    if _cached_key is None or (now - _fetched_at) > TTL_SECONDS:\n        with _lock:\n            # Double-checked locking\n            if _cached_key is None or (now - _fetched_at) > TTL_SECONDS:\n                _cached_key = _fetch_from_ssm()\n                _fetched_at = now\n    return _cached_key\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/llm_client.py\nimport anthropic\nfrom src.api_key import get_api_key\n\ndef create_client() -> anthropic.Anthropic:\n    \"\"\"Always create a fresh client so key rotations are picked up.\"\"\"\n    return anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=get_api_key())\n\ndef complete(prompt: str, max_tokens: int = 1024) -> str:\n    client = create_client()\n    msg = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=max_tokens,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return msg.content[0].text\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated Rotation Script"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A rotation script can be run manually or scheduled via a cron job / GitHub Actions workflow. It wraps the five-step sequence and exits with a non-zero code if any step fails:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"rotate_api_key.py \u2014 zero-downtime Claude API key rotation.\"\"\"\nimport os, sys, time\nimport boto3\nimport anthropic\n\nPARAM_NAME  = os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_KEY_PARAM\"]   # e.g. /prod/claude/api_key\nAWS_REGION  = os.environ[\"AWS_REGION\"]\nOVERLAP_SEC = int(os.environ.get(\"ROTATION_OVERLAP_SEC\", \"5400\"))  # 90 min default\n\nssm = boto3.client(\"ssm\", region_name=AWS_REGION)\n\ndef current_key() -> str:\n    return ssm.get_parameter(Name=PARAM_NAME, WithDecryption=True)[\"Parameter\"][\"Value\"]\n\ndef write_key(key: str) -> None:\n    ssm.put_parameter(Name=PARAM_NAME, Value=key, Type=\"SecureString\", Overwrite=True)\n    print(f\"SSM parameter updated: {PARAM_NAME}\")\n\ndef health_check(key: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Send a minimal request to verify the key is accepted.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=key)\n        client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n            max_tokens=1,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"ping\"}],\n        )\n        return True\n    except anthropic.AuthenticationError:\n        return False\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Health check error (non-auth): {e}\")\n        return True   # non-auth errors don't indicate key failure\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    old_key = current_key()\n    print(f\"Old key: ...{old_key[-6:]}\")\n\n    # Step 1: Create new key via Anthropic API\n    # Note: key creation is done via the Anthropic Console API or admin SDK.\n    # Here we read the new key from an env var set by the operator / CI.\n    new_key = os.environ.get(\"NEW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\")\n    if not new_key:\n        print(\"ERROR: NEW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not set. Generate a new key in the Console first.\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(f\"New key: ...{new_key[-6:]}\")\n\n    # Step 2: Health-check new key before writing\n    print(\"Verifying new key with Anthropic API...\")\n    if not health_check(new_key):\n        print(\"ERROR: New key health check failed \u2014 aborting rotation\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(\"New key verified.\")\n\n    # Step 3: Write new key to secrets store\n    write_key(new_key)\n\n    # Step 4: Wait for all app instances to refresh (overlap window)\n    print(f\"Waiting {OVERLAP_SEC}s for instances to pick up new key...\")\n    time.sleep(OVERLAP_SEC)\n\n    # Step 5: Confirm new key still works (instances have refreshed)\n    if not health_check(new_key):\n        print(\"ERROR: New key failed health check post-overlap \u2014 do not revoke old key\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    print(f\"Rotation complete. Revoke old key ...{old_key[-6:]} manually in the Anthropic Console.\")\n    print(\"IMPORTANT: Do not revoke until you have confirmed zero errors in production metrics.\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The script intentionally does not auto-revoke the old key \u2014 that step requires human confirmation after checking error rates in the monitoring dashboard."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scheduled Rotation via GitHub Actions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/rotate-api-key.yml\nname: Rotate Claude API Key\n\non:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 2 1 * *'   # 02:00 UTC on the 1st of each month\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      new_key:\n        description: 'New Anthropic API key (from Console)'\n        required: true\n\njobs:\n  rotate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: production   # requires manual approval\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Configure AWS credentials (OIDC)\n        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v4\n        with:\n          role-to-assume: ${{ secrets.AWS_ROTATION_ROLE_ARN }}\n          aws-region: us-east-1\n\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: pip install anthropic boto3\n\n      - name: Run rotation\n        env:\n          ANTHROPIC_KEY_PARAM: /prod/claude/api_key\n          AWS_REGION: us-east-1\n          NEW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ github.event.inputs.new_key || secrets.PENDING_NEW_API_KEY }}\n          ROTATION_OVERLAP_SEC: \"5400\"\n        run: python3 scripts/rotate_api_key.py\n\n      - name: Post to Slack\n        if: always()\n        env:\n          SLACK_WEBHOOK: ${{ secrets.SLACK_OPS_WEBHOOK }}\n        run: |\n          STATUS=\"${{ job.status }}\"\n          curl -s -X POST \"$SLACK_WEBHOOK\" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n            -d \"{\\\"text\\\": \\\":key: API key rotation *${STATUS}*. Check production error rate before revoking old key.\\\"}\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key-per-Workload Isolation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A single API key shared across all workloads means that any rotation or compromise affects all workloads simultaneously. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key-per-workload isolation",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " assigns a separate key to each distinct service or environment:"
          }
        ]
      },
