      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits of isolation: a compromised CI key cannot be used to make production calls; rotating the prod key does not break the eval pipeline; usage costs are attributable per workload; and a leaked dev key can be revoked without touching production."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/api_key.py \u2014 workload-aware key selection\nimport os\n\n# Set WORKLOAD env var per deployment: prod, staging, ci, batch\nWORKLOAD = os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD\", \"prod\")\n\nPARAM_MAP = {\n    \"prod\":    \"/prod/claude/api_key\",\n    \"staging\": \"/staging/claude/api_key\",\n    \"ci\":      \"/ci/claude/api_key\",\n    \"batch\":   \"/batch/claude/api_key\",\n}\n\ndef _param_name() -> str:\n    param = PARAM_MAP.get(WORKLOAD)\n    if param is None:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown WORKLOAD: '{WORKLOAD}'. Set to one of {list(PARAM_MAP)}\")\n    return param\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Leaked Keys Before Rotation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Proactively scan for accidentally committed keys before they are used maliciously. TruffleHog detects Anthropic key patterns in git history:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/secret-scan.yml\nname: Secret Scan\n\non: [push, pull_request]\n\njobs:\n  trufflehog:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0   # full history for git log scanning\n\n      - name: TruffleHog scan\n        uses: trufflesecurity/trufflehog@main\n        with:\n          path: ./\n          base: ${{ github.event.repository.default_branch }}\n          head: HEAD\n          extra_args: --only-verified\n"
          }
        ]
      },
